 Munster, the earl of Clanricarde in Connacht and Lord Montgomery in Ulster, as well as the Confederate Catholic engagement with popular politics. The role of the marquess of Ormond, the Irish Parliament and the Church of Ireland are also examined in new ways, and the volume ends with a fresh look at the war of words between Oliver Cromwell and the Catholic Church. Ireland in crisis presents a very different view of the period that challenges existing assumptions. It will appeal to lecturers, students and the general reader.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  aAdventurers.  aCatholic.  aClanricarde.  aClotworthy.  aConfederate.  aCromwell.  aIreland.  aOrmond.  aParliament.  aUlster.1 aBrown, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarcy, Eamon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDennehy, Coleman A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuignan, Aoife, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForkan, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLittle, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLittle, Patrick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcGrath, Bríd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorrill, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobinson, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612671940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/